<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-10-09T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-10-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="404" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d404">
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. Hunter</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Bigelow</persName></head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 283.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi></placeName>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1865-10-09"><hi rend="italic">October</hi> 9, 1865.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> Your despatch of the 21st ultimo, No. 177,
                            containing an account of your conversation with Mr. Drouyn de Lhuys in
                            regard to the reduction of the French forces in Mexico, has been
                            received, and will be taken into consideration. An instruction of the
                            20th ultimo, No. 264, will have placed you in possession of the views of
                            this government in regard to the compulsory transportation of Egyptian
                            negro troops by France to Mexico.</p>
                        <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>W. HUNTER, <hi rend="italic">Acting
                            Secretary.</hi></signed></closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">John Bigelow,</hi> Esq,, <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi></p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>